snippet.textDisplay: Kinda interesting, the crosswalk noise that they employed here. Not to compare these two acts/artists, but notably, for the main hook of the song "Rattle That Lock," David Gilmour used the jingle from the French National Railway Company that he recorded on his iPhone while he was traveling. The four-note jingle is played at French railway stations prior to announcements being made; Dave thought it sounded catchy, and held his phone up to one of the speakers to record it, and boom -- there was the foundation of a new song. Kinda cool how that works out sometimes!
